# TEAM AND TEAM DYNAMICS

### Notes:
Definition of a team
Group of members who must rely on group work to achieve success.
Members in a team are organised around a common set of objectives and their work is mutually dependent.
Team Dynamics
In talking about workplace relationships, one can’t avoid paying much attention to work-team relationships.
This is because the nature of work these days often require people to work in teams.
Working in teams allows individuals from different areas of work (e.g. Marketing and IT) with different roles (staff, volunteer and customer) and even from different organisations to work together.
The dynamics of what makes teams work and how a group of individuals can create the synergy to achieve positive outcomes as a team is called Team Dynamics.
Understanding team dynamics is useful in helping you navigate team relationships at the workplace.
Team dynamics describes the behavioral relationships between the members of a group.
The dynamic between them includes how they interact, communicate and cooperate with one another.
How well your team is able to do these things directly influences what it can accomplish.
