### Notes:
Developing a Team
Good team dynamics is crucial to effective teamwork.
The old acronym TEAM, “Together everyone achieves more,” is as true today as it ever was.
Teamwork is a cooperative effort in which individual interests are subordinated to the interests and needs of the team.
If a team is to reach its potential, each player must be willing to subordinate his personal goals to the good of the team.
This means “giving up some of the me for the we.”
Teams go through 5 stages of development (Bruce Tuckman model)
- 1. Forming
- 2. Storming
- 3. Norming
- 4. Performing
- 5. Adjourning
The stages start from the time that a team first meets until the project ends.
