### Notes:
Stage 3 - Norming
During the norming stage, people start to appreciate their team members’ strengths and make progress together.
Strategy
Remind yourself of the other teammates’ strengths and expertise, and avoid magnifying what you don’t like about them.
For example, while you may still think that your tech guy’s choice in music is obnoxious, you also admire his knowledge of web design and coding skills, and value his opinions on anything tech-related.
Storming sometimes overlaps with norming.
Be prepared to tackle new conflicts as they may arise from new tasks or new instructions from the boss.
But since you’ve already dealt with disagreement before, it will probably be easier to address this time.
