### Notes:
Stage 5 - Adjourning
Once a project ends, the team disbands.
This phase is sometimes known as mourning because members have grown close and feel a loss now that the experience is over.
However, stay connected if you can, for you don’t know when the next project will bring everyone back together again!
It is also good to take stock of what you have learnt from:
How your teammates have contributed with their expertise and knowledge
How conflicts were resolved successfully / unsuccessfully
