### Notes:
When are conflicts unhealthy?
When conflicts are not managed properly, they will continue to affect the involved parties and even the entire team later.
Unresolved conflicts will cause unhealthy behaviour and collateral damages overtime, such as:
- Lower the morale of the involved parties and the other teammates, thereby lowering overall productivity.
- Cause more conflicts (as people are ever more sensitive to their needs and what they disapprove of the other party).
- Cause inappropriate behaviour, such as avoiding communication, being self-serving, isolation at work, blaming and putting others down.
Therefore, it is best to engage conflicts early before they begin to sabotage the workplace relationship.
Resolving conflicts not only helps solve current problems, but also potential future ones which are rooted in the same causes.
When conflicts are resolved, it helps build a stronger company culture grounded in trust and respect, where employees can feel safe to disagree and admit to mistakes without facing huge personal repercussions.
