# Resolving Conflicts
### Notes:
Resolving Conflicts
The goal of conflict resolution is not to decide which person is right or wrong.
Rather, it is to reach a solution that everyone can live with.
It is important not to rush into finding solution before discover needs first.
Here are some tips on resolving conflicts.
Finding Needs
- 1. Acknowledge that a difficult situation exists
People must first acknowledge that what is happening is causing problem to their work.
Without which, it will be difficult for people to understand the need to proactively change their perspectives or the way they work.
- 2. Let people express their feelings
People usually get feelings of anger and hurt in conflict situations.
It is difficult for rational problem-solving thinking when people are preoccupied by strong feelings.
Expressing feelings help people release their emotional stress, and also help them feel better by allowing the other party to acknowledge those emotions.
- 3. Let people express their views
The parties on both sides of the conflict may have different assumptions or views on the causes of the conflict and what should be done.
This is a chance to identify gaps in information or incompatible beliefs, goals, and values.
Once we understand why people want the solution they initially proposed, we can discover their needs more easily.
