# Resolving Conflicts
### Notes:
Solutioning
- 4. Find common areas of agreement, no matter how small
To find a solution that everyone can agree on, first find what people can agree on first.
- The procedure to follow
- Their worst fears: budget overrun, project failure, betraying the boss’ trust, bonus cut.
- Their loyalty to the team
- Their strengths
Agreeing on some smaller areas give an experience of success and help people agree on bigger changes later.
- 5. Find solutions to satisfy needs
Discover the root cause of the problem by focusing on the problem and not on each other.
The parties can try generating multiple alternatives to tackle the causes and determine which actions will be taken.
However, it is important for the involved parties to give their real agreement.
