# FIVE CONFLICT HANDLING STYLES

### Notes:
Conflict-Handling Styles
There are five common styles of handling conflicts.
Since there is no one “right style” to deal with conflicts, employing different styles to match the situation is key to successful conflict resolution.
For example, someone may want to back down from an argument with an agitated queue-cutter to avoid getting into a “raging” situation.
However, he/she would want to confront the boss who docks pay without warning or reason.
