# ACCOMMODATING

Win-Lose
Sacrifice one’s goal
When outcome is unimportant
### Notes:
Accommodating
One party obliges or willingly give in to meet the needs of the other party.
Done at the expense of one accommodating party’s own needs or desires.
Works well when the one who accommodates does not bother much about the loss.
Is a win-lose style
The one who accommodates loses while the other party wins.
Over time, this can cause frustration to build and leads to an expectation among the assertive party that they'll always get their way.
Examples of when to use
Want to keep the peace
Feel as though you are in the wrong
Accommodating people can be encouraged to state their needs to move toward collaboration.
