### Notes:
Competing
One party focuses on own problem to the exclusion of the other party’s until one side gives in or is defeated.
Due to a party having no interest in compromising, collaborating or avoiding the conflict.
It is used when action has to be carried out quickly or when unpopular decisions have to be taken.
Is a win-lose style
It gives the winner a sense of victory while the loser feels defeated.
Causes frustration among colleagues who want their views taken seriously too.
