### Notes:
Compromising
Both parties settle their differences through a give-and-take approach.
Requires everyone to make sacrifices to achieve partial resolution.
Aim is to find a solution that is deemed fair and can at least partially please all parties.
Is a weak win-win style
Both parties are happy with the outcome where their goals are met/partially met.
Beware that a fair solution is not always an effective solution.
Examples of when to use
Need a temporary solution
Break an impasse
Meet a rapidly approaching deadline
This style is still too focused on competition. Parties should work towards collaboration for longer term resolution.
