### Notes:
Collaborating
Both parties cooperate closely to find a solution that will meet the needs of all parties.
The team cooperates to meet everyone’s needs to the greatest extent possible, not just a middle ground.
Time-consuming and the parties concerned must be able to state their needs clearly.
Is a win-win style
Creates a collaborative environment where people are willing to state their needs and help meet the needs of others.
This style can actually enhance interpersonal relationships and encourage new ideas.
Examples of when to use
There is an important relationship present between the parties
The final solution is too important for anyone to be displeased
To properly represent all the stakeholders
Although it may not always be possible, it is worth striving for.
